    "minides": "India's most affordable two-door electric sports convertible — 510 PS, 725 Nm, 0-100 in 3.2 sec, scissor doors, and 580 km MIDC range. Sold exclusively through MG Select.",
    "description": "Launched in India in July 2025 via MG's premium MG Select dealerships, the MG Cyberster is India's first mass-market electric roadster convertible and the spiritual successor to the iconic MGB. Priced at ₹82.50 lakh (ex-showroom), it is offered in a single fully-loaded GT variant — a CBU import — powered by a 77 kWh dual-motor AWD drivetrain producing 510 PS and 725 Nm for a 0-100 km/h time of 3.2 seconds. The Cyberster's headline features include electric scissor frameless doors with remote operation, a 10-second electrically operated soft-top convertible roof (operable up to 50 km/h), a triple-screen cockpit (two driver-facing displays + passenger screen), Brembo disc brakes on all four corners, 144 kW DC fast charging (10-80% in 40 min), Level 2 ADAS, 360-degree camera, and an electronic differential lock for performance driving. 350+ units sold in India within the first year of launch. Available in 5 colours: Flare Red, Nuclear Yellow, Andes Grey, Modern Beige, and the new Irises Cyan added January 2026."
  },
